title: Tennis | Fox News
description: Tennis is one of the most popular sports in the world. Its four majors include the Australian Open, French Open, Wimbledon and U.S. Open. Top players include Roger Federer, Serena Williams and Rafa Nadal.

Texas Attorney General Ken Paxton launched an investigation into the U.S. Tennis Association Texas League over possible transgender participation in women's matches.
World No. 1 Aryna Sabalenka will face Nick Kyrgios in a special exhibition tennis match on Dec. 28 in Dubai, featuring modified rules for an exciting showdown.
American tennis star Danielle Collins raised eyebrows with her dating profile as she looked to find love on the apps instead of having ot turn to reality TV.
Aryna Sabalenka's racket throw nearly hit a ballboy during her semifinal loss to Jessica Pegula at the Wuhan Open tennis tournament in China.
Alexis Ohanian confronted Stephen A. Smith on ESPN's "First Take" about marriage advice Smith previously gave regarding Ohanian's relationship with Serena Williams.
Martina Navratilova expressed objection through X posts after Disney indefinitely preempted Jimmy Kimmel's show over his comments about Tyler Robinson.
American tennis star Taylor Townsend faced fierce backlash in China after she criticized the food in a series of post on social media, prompting the doubles player to issue an apology.
Russian tennis star Anna Kalinskaya claimed the Danish men's player Holger Rune was in her direct messages about "10 times" asking her on a date.
President Donald Trump on Sunday was seen signing autographs for tennis fans before he departed the U.S. Open in New York City. Carlos Alcaraz won the tournament.
The "Drake curse" reared its ugly head on Sunday in a totally unbelievable way. See how he lost over half-a-million bucks.
President Donald Trump was the main attraction in the stands at the U.S. Open in New York City and some of his fiercest critics were also in attendance.
President Donald Trump received a mix of applause and boos on Sunday as he arrived at the U.S. Open men's singles final between Jannik Sinner and Carlos Alcaraz.
Carlos Alcaraz won the second U.S. Open title of his career on Sunday as he defeated Jannik Sinner in four sets with President Donald Trump watching.
President Donald Trump arrived at the U.S. Open in New York City on Sunday ahead of the men's singles final between Jannik Sinner and Carlos Alcaraz.
TV networks were reportedly told to avoid airing any reactions from U.S. Open fans toward President Donald Trump during the men's singles final on Sunday.
Belarusian Aryna Sabalenka dominated American tennis star Amanda Anisimova to win the 2025 U.S. Open on Saturday night. It's her second straight tournament win.
The U.S. Open, known for its A-list attendees, will see President Donald Trump in attendance for Sunday's men's singles final between Carlos Alcaraz and Jannik Sinner.
President Donald Trump will attend the U.S. Open men's final on Sunday, a White House official confirmed to Fox News on Thursday night.
American tennis star Amanda Anisimova is one win away from winning the U.S. Open after beating Naomi Osaka in the semifinals on Thursday. Who is she?
Polish tennis star Iga Swiatek got into a testy exchange with a reporter after she lost in straight sets to American Amanda Anisimova at the U.S. Open.
The crowd at the U.S. Open on Tuesday night briefly rattled Serbian tennis star Novak Djokovic during his four-set victory over American Taylor Fritz.
Venus Williams made it all the way to the quarterfinals of the women's U.S. Open doubles bracket before her impressive run ended with a loss on Tuesday night.
Coco Gauff suffered an emotional upset loss to Naomi Osaka, 3-6, 2-6, in the U.S. Open Round of 16, with the No. 3 seed admitting she broke down after the match.
Aryna Sabalenka, the world's No. 1 women's tennis player, says tequila is "better on the body," though doctors emphasize all alcohol carries health risks.
Naomi Osaka reached her first Grand Slam quarterfinals since 2021, eliminating American star Coco Gauff in straight sets at the 2025 U.S. Open on Monday.
Spanish tennis player Jaume Munar defeated Belgium's Zizou Bergs in straight sets at the U.S. Open, but the match ended with a heated exchange at the net.
Andrey Rublev received a $3,000 fine for using foul language during his U.S. Open second-round match and believes the penalty for self-directed comments is unfair.
Latvian tennis star Jelena Ostapenko issued an apology on social media for the comments she made at American Taylor Townsend at the U.S. Open.
Czech tennis star Karolina Muchova admitted to being thrown off when she saw her ex-boyfriend in the crowd of Thursday's match at the U.S. Open.
A man proposed to his girlfriend during a U.S. Open match between Aryna Sabalenka and Leylah Fernandez on Friday night in New York City.
